{{zh-see|傅|ss}}

====Usage notes====
{{lang|zh|付}} was included as the simplified form of {{l|zh|傅}} in the {{w|Second round of simplified Chinese characters|second round of simplification}} in 1977. The current standard in Mainland China, the {{w|Table of General Standard Chinese Characters}} ({{lw|zh|通用规范汉字表}}), does not mention that {{lang|zh|付}} is a simplification of {{l|zh|傅}}. ''{{w|A Dictionary of Current Chinese}}'' ({{lw|zh|现代汉语词典}}) and the ''Xinhua Dictionary'' ({{lw|zh|新华字典}}) list {{lang|zh|付}} as a separate entry from {{l|zh|傅}} (unlike other variants, which are usually put beside the main character in parentheses) and define {{lang|zh|付}} as a common variant for {{l|zh|傅}}, while ''{{w|Xiandai Hanyu Guifan Cidian}}'' ({{lw|zh|pref=《|现代汉语规范词典|suf=》}}) proscribes the use of {{lang|zh|付}} as the simplified form of {{l|zh|傅}}.

Similar to the surnames {{zh-l|肖|tr=-}} and {{zh-l|蕭|tr=-}}, the surname {{l-self|zh|付}} and {{zh-l|傅|tr=-}} were also originally distinct, and {{l-self|zh|付}} was originally a rare surname. The modern surname {{l-self|zh|付}} is mostly due to second-round simplification of Chinese characters.

